<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
          
   <p n="1">
      Prosperity! Fortune!
   </p>
   
   <p n="1-4">
      Fifteenth year of the victorious king Nantivikkiramaparumar.<note>Sanskrit Nandivikramavarman.</note>
   </p>
   
   <p n="4-12">
      <gap reason="lost"/>,
      the son <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied>
      <gap reason="lost"/>,
      the lord of the temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>taḷi-y-uṭaiya</foreign></supplied>, who lives in Veṇpēṭu
      <gap reason="lost"/>
      with <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>koṇṭu</foreign></supplied> the capital <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mutal</foreign></supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">of one</supplied> <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign> <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> gold
      <supplied reason="subaudible">deposited</supplied> with <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iṭai</foreign><note>Literally, "in the place of."</note></supplied> Puraicar Mōṭaṉ <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Mulaṅkūr,
      this gold
      <gap reason="lost"/>
   </p>
   
